main event: A rocket-shaped white object appeared at the horizon, climbed 35 degrees above the horizon, and was visible for one minute and 30 seconds.
interesting points: The object appeared as an elongated light and had fire coming from its tail exhaust.
The object hovered at a distance of about a mile at arm's length.
The report states the object was probably a balloon, but the reporting officer concurs it was an unidentified missile.
There were no photographs included in the report.
The report mentions other witnesses, including an officer and guard detail, who also sighted the object from a different location.
